function.name: sqlmap
function.description: Performs a SQL lookup for a given key with a given SQL query.

function_description.name: sqlmap
function_description.description: Does a lookup in a SQL table via a prepared SQL statement, i.e., the statement needs to include some variable parts. Furthermore, the connection string to the SQL database can be defined via the following attributes: 'databaseType' = the type of the database, e.g., 'mysql'; 'host' = the host of the database, e.g., 'localhost' (default = 'localhost'); 'port' = the port of the database, e.g., '3306' (default = '3306'); 'database' = the name of the database. The credentials for the connection can be defined with the following attributes: 'login' = the username that should be utilised to connect to the database; 'password' = the password that should be utilised to connect to the database. The SQL query statement that should be utilised to retrieve the value for a given key can be defined via 'query', e.g. 'SELECT value FROM mytable WHERE key = ?'. The driver that should be utilised to establish the connection to the database can be defined via 'driver' (default = 'com.mysql.jdbc.Driver'; note: the database driver needs to be part of the classpath of the execution environment).

host.description: the host of the database, e.g., localhost (default = localhost)

port.description: the port of the database, e.g., 3306 (default = 3306)

login.description: the username that should be utilised to connect to the database

password.description: the password that should be utilised to connect to the database

query.description: the prepared SQL statement that should be utilised to retrieve the value for a given key, e.g. 'SELECT value FROM mytable WHERE key = ?'

driver.description: the JDBC driver that should be utilised to connect to the database (default = com.mysql.jdbc.Driver; note: the database driver needs to be part of the classpath of the execution environment)

parameter_mappings.query: SELECT name FROM DATA_SCHEMA WHERE uuid = ?

function.name: combine
function.description: Collects all received values and combine them. This function does only emit values, when all sources emit something.
